1
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:48,333
[alarm rings]

2
00:00:52,083 --> 00:00:54,666
[KOBAYASHI groans]

3
00:00:54,750 --> 00:00:57,208
Oh, my head...

4
00:00:57,291 --> 00:00:59,041
Hangovers suck...

5
00:01:10,791 --> 00:01:12,541
[KOBAYASHI]
Ooh, cold!

6
00:01:14,166 --> 00:01:16,208
Come check out Maid Café: Cozy.

7
00:01:16,291 --> 00:01:18,208
Stop by and say hi!

8
00:01:18,291 --> 00:01:20,583
Hope to see you
at Maid Café: Cozy!

9
00:01:20,666 --> 00:01:22,833
[KOBAYASH gulps, sighs]

10
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:24,875
Man. My lower back hurts, too...

11
00:01:27,375 --> 00:01:28,916
[KOBAYASHI] Running that
new integration test

12
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:31,250
should be a straight-up
blast today.

13
00:01:42,041 --> 00:01:45,791
[DRAGON growls]

14
00:01:45,875 --> 00:01:48,916
[roars]

15
00:01:50,291 --> 00:01:52,375
[gasps]

16
00:01:52,458 --> 00:01:53,416
[KOBAYASHI]
Dragons.

17
00:01:53,500 --> 00:01:56,916
The most powerful of all beings.

18
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:59,291
An imaginary creature
that has giant wings

19
00:01:59,375 --> 00:02:03,125
for flight, possesses magical
powers, and breathes fire.

20
00:02:05,625 --> 00:02:07,791
Ah! Ta-dah!

21
00:02:07,875 --> 00:02:09,041
[giggles]

22
00:02:15,916 --> 00:02:17,208
[giggles]

23
00:02:17,291 --> 00:02:19,541
[KOBAYASHI]
Although, what do I know?

24
00:03:55,625 --> 00:03:57,916
Having a good morning,
Miss Kobayashi?

25
00:04:02,916 --> 00:04:04,250
I don't know yet.

26
00:04:04,333 --> 00:04:06,625
Do you mind allowing
me in to your lovely home?

27
00:04:06,708 --> 00:04:08,833
Oh. Sure, why the heck not?

28
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:10,500
[door bell rings]

29
00:04:11,791 --> 00:04:13,250
So, you say we met yesterday,

30
00:04:13,333 --> 00:04:15,083
and I offered to
let you stay here.

31
00:04:15,166 --> 00:04:18,333
With me. And you're for sure
positive that's what I said?

32
00:04:18,416 --> 00:04:20,166
Indeed!

33
00:04:20,250 --> 00:04:21,250
[KOBAYASHI]
This is weird.

34
00:04:21,333 --> 00:04:23,291
Why am I not waking up
from this dream?

35
00:04:23,375 --> 00:04:26,958
Unless it's not a dream.
There's no way.

36
00:04:28,458 --> 00:04:30,750
So, um...
Remind me where we met?

37
00:04:30,833 --> 00:04:34,750
The mountains!
We met in the mountains!

38
00:04:34,833 --> 00:04:35,666
Mountains...

39
00:04:35,750 --> 00:04:37,750
[KOBAYASHI laughs]

40
00:04:37,833 --> 00:04:40,375
[KOBAYASHI]
I remember mountains.

41
00:04:40,458 --> 00:04:42,458
Okay, it's coming back.

42
00:04:44,875 --> 00:04:46,333
[KOBAYASHI]
A dragon?

43
00:04:47,833 --> 00:04:50,333
[KOBAYASHI]
Apparently, a hilarious dragon.

44
00:04:50,416 --> 00:04:51,625
Oh, God...

45
00:04:54,791 --> 00:04:57,458
So, wanna stay
with me, "dragon"?

46
00:04:57,541 --> 00:04:59,333
[echoes] So, wanna
stay with me, "dragon"?

47
00:04:59,416 --> 00:05:00,500
[gasps]

48
00:05:00,583 --> 00:05:03,708
I'll never forget
those wondrous words!

49
00:05:03,791 --> 00:05:05,458
I can begin working
as your personal maid

50
00:05:05,541 --> 00:05:07,083
immediately if you want!

51
00:05:07,166 --> 00:05:08,583
[KOBAYASHI]
Oh, that's a big negative.

52
00:05:08,666 --> 00:05:09,958
Huh?

53
00:05:10,041 --> 00:05:11,625
[KOBAYASHI] I'm not like
a dragon racist or anything.

54
00:05:11,708 --> 00:05:14,208
I'm just not in the market
right now to hire a maid.

55
00:05:14,291 --> 00:05:17,333
[TOHRU gasps] But!
You wouldn't have to pay me!

56
00:05:17,416 --> 00:05:18,833
Yeah, no, that's not really--

57
00:05:18,916 --> 00:05:21,125
Listen, I can be super helpful!

58
00:05:21,208 --> 00:05:23,166
I can turn this
area into a sea of fire,

59
00:05:23,250 --> 00:05:24,375
or curse people to death!

60
00:05:24,458 --> 00:05:25,875
[KOBAYASHI]
No, no, no!

61
00:05:25,958 --> 00:05:27,666
But, why maid instead of that?

62
00:05:27,750 --> 00:05:30,166
Because you said a maid
would work better for you!

63
00:05:30,250 --> 00:05:31,666
I did, huh?

64
00:05:35,666 --> 00:05:38,166
Yeah, does make sense...

65
00:05:40,083 --> 00:05:41,166
I'm sorry, Tohru.

66
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:43,500
I shouldn't have
made that promise.

67
00:05:43,583 --> 00:05:45,708
No one can change
the impossible.

68
00:05:45,791 --> 00:05:47,875
It's not, like, personal.

69
00:05:47,958 --> 00:05:49,791
[TOHRU gasps]

70
00:05:53,541 --> 00:05:54,791
Are you certain...?

71
00:05:54,875 --> 00:05:56,541
It's impossible?

72
00:05:56,625 --> 00:05:58,958
[KOBAYASHI]
Mm-hmm... Sorry.

73
00:06:02,583 --> 00:06:04,166
I understand.

74
00:06:04,250 --> 00:06:07,416
My apologies as well,
for dropping in so suddenly.

75
00:06:17,833 --> 00:06:18,875
[gasps]

76
00:06:21,416 --> 00:06:23,791
Wanna stay with me, "dragon"?

77
00:06:25,583 --> 00:06:28,333
[KOBAYASHI] Why won't this
stupid guilt go away?

78
00:06:31,250 --> 00:06:35,416
[KOBAYASHI] Maybe this dream...
is really not a dream.

79
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:37,916
And if it's not, then...

80
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:43,541
I'm late?! Tohru!

81
00:06:43,625 --> 00:06:44,833
[TOHRU]
Ah?

82
00:06:44,916 --> 00:06:48,416
[pants]
Can you fly?!

83
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:50,250
[gasps]

84
00:06:50,333 --> 00:06:51,291
Ah!

85
00:06:51,375 --> 00:06:57,958
[KOBAYASHI screams]

86
00:06:58,041 --> 00:07:00,000
Dragons are so fast!

87
00:07:00,083 --> 00:07:01,541
[TOHRU]
Sorry, what did you say?

88
00:07:01,625 --> 00:07:04,000
You're hella fast!

89
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:10,333
I could keep her.

90
00:07:10,416 --> 00:07:11,416
[TOHRU]
Are you serious?!

91
00:07:11,500 --> 00:07:13,125
So, now you can hear me?

92
00:07:15,875 --> 00:07:17,458
[KOBAYASHI] I guess it wouldn't
be the end of the world

93
00:07:17,541 --> 00:07:19,833
to have someone
around the house.

94
00:07:19,916 --> 00:07:20,958
And if she's there--

95
00:07:21,041 --> 00:07:22,666
[yelps]

96
00:07:22,750 --> 00:07:24,958
This is murdering my lower back!

97
00:07:29,166 --> 00:07:31,541
[KOBAYASHI] Okay.
First, let's take a look at

98
00:07:31,625 --> 00:07:33,666
what you've decided is
the proper outfit for a maid

99
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:35,083
and why that's totally wrong.

100
00:07:35,166 --> 00:07:36,708
Great idea!

101
00:07:36,791 --> 00:07:37,875
Here you go.

102
00:07:37,958 --> 00:07:41,083
--Huh...?
--It's says Maid Café Cozy, see?

103
00:07:41,166 --> 00:07:42,583
What is this?

104
00:07:42,666 --> 00:07:44,583
I discovered some real life
maids while on my way here.

105
00:07:44,666 --> 00:07:46,791
Meaning we'll have
to start from scratch.

106
00:07:46,875 --> 00:07:49,333
First thing, as
a housemaid--you clean.

107
00:07:49,416 --> 00:07:51,083
Oh, I'm good at cleaning!

108
00:07:54,208 --> 00:07:56,125
--How's that?
--No! It's all gone!

109
00:07:56,208 --> 00:07:57,166
[TOHRU]
One moment!

110
00:07:57,250 --> 00:07:58,166
[KOBAYASHI]
You can bring it back?

111
00:07:58,250 --> 00:08:00,875
Next! Laundry maid!
Do laundry.

112
00:08:00,958 --> 00:08:02,666
I can handle that, too!

113
00:08:04,083 --> 00:08:05,291
[muffled]
I can produce a saliva

114
00:08:05,375 --> 00:08:07,416
that specifically
removes stains.

115
00:08:07,500 --> 00:08:09,666
[KOBAYASHI]
Gross! No one wants to see that!

116
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:12,291
Next! Parlor maid!
Greet people.

117
00:08:12,375 --> 00:08:13,708
Easy thing for me!

118
00:08:13,791 --> 00:08:14,958
[doorbell]

119
00:08:15,041 --> 00:08:16,833
Hi, I just need
a signature for this delivery.

120
00:08:16,916 --> 00:08:19,833
The foolish, inferior human
is not welcome at this home!

121
00:08:19,916 --> 00:08:21,625
--Hey.
--Oh, you're an exception

122
00:08:21,708 --> 00:08:23,250
of course, Miss Kobayashi!

123
00:08:23,333 --> 00:08:25,541
[KOBAYASHI]
Last one! Kitchen maid.

124
00:08:25,625 --> 00:08:28,083
--You cook.
--Cooking is my specialty!

125
00:08:29,166 --> 00:08:31,375
Try my very own roasted tail!

126
00:08:31,458 --> 00:08:32,666
[KOBAYASHI]
No, thanks.

127
00:08:32,750 --> 00:08:34,458
--[TOHRU] Huh?
--[KOBAYASHI] No way.

128
00:08:34,541 --> 00:08:35,583
Wha--?!

129
00:08:35,666 --> 00:08:37,416
Would you prefer it
well-done instead?

130
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:38,666
[KOBAYASHI]
That's not the problem.

131
00:08:38,750 --> 00:08:40,666
Then I'm confident
you'll enjoy it immensely!

132
00:08:40,750 --> 00:08:42,416
I'm ethically
against dragon tail.

133
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:45,166
Ah-hah! Seems you're
a picky eater, Miss Kobayashi!

134
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:46,208
Dragon logic.

135
00:08:46,291 --> 00:08:49,833
[TOHRU growling]

136
00:08:49,916 --> 00:08:50,958
[gulps]

137
00:08:52,750 --> 00:08:53,750
[KOBAYASHI]
It grows back?!

138
00:08:53,833 --> 00:08:55,083
Took a bit longer
than usual because

139
00:08:55,166 --> 00:08:56,250
I had to remove all the poison.

140
00:08:56,333 --> 00:08:57,541
[KOBAYASHI]
And it's poisonous?!

141
00:08:59,541 --> 00:09:01,416
Hate to break it to you,
but you don't know how to maid.

142
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:03,625
[gasps] Then, I'll learn
from the ground up!

143
00:09:03,708 --> 00:09:06,833
Shall we start my education with
you telling me what you dislike?

144
00:09:06,916 --> 00:09:10,333
What I dislike?
I can't do <i>hijiki</i> or eggplant.

145
00:09:10,416 --> 00:09:12,583
Interesting.
I'll remember that.

146
00:09:12,666 --> 00:09:14,625
Personally, I dislike
eggs when the yolks

147
00:09:14,708 --> 00:09:15,833
have been removed.

148
00:09:15,916 --> 00:09:17,791
A while back, I had
a friend named Herensuge

149
00:09:17,875 --> 00:09:19,000
who was hit with one and killed.

150
00:09:19,083 --> 00:09:20,791
[KOBAYASHI]
That's a powerful egg.

151
00:09:20,875 --> 00:09:23,291
Hold up. Why are you
asking about dislikes?

152
00:09:23,375 --> 00:09:25,416
Shouldn't you ask what I like?

153
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:27,291
No, that's bad luck.

154
00:09:27,375 --> 00:09:29,833
Unfortunately, I've had
far too many friends slain

155
00:09:29,916 --> 00:09:31,500
by the very things
they love most.

156
00:09:31,583 --> 00:09:33,833
You know--liquor and women
and jewels and such.

157
00:09:33,916 --> 00:09:35,708
Sounds a lot like humans.

158
00:09:35,791 --> 00:09:38,583
However, I can certainly
let you know one thing I like!

159
00:09:38,666 --> 00:09:41,083
It's you! I love you,
Miss Kobayashi!

160
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:43,083
You gonna eat me?

161
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:45,041
[TOHRU] No, not like that!
Like sexually!

162
00:09:45,125 --> 00:09:46,958
I'm not into women or dragons.

163
00:09:47,041 --> 00:09:49,583
Yes, but I can't put a label
on what I feel for you!

164
00:09:49,666 --> 00:09:52,916
You saved me, and I'll use my
whole body to repay the favor!

165
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:55,666
Please use me to commute
to work again tomorrow!

166
00:09:55,750 --> 00:09:58,541
Thanks, but I got enough of
that earlier. You're hard.

167
00:09:58,625 --> 00:10:00,208
Gimme a chance, Miss Kobayashi!

168
00:10:00,291 --> 00:10:03,000
I was raised to pay back all
favors, even if they were only

169
00:10:03,083 --> 00:10:05,541
owed to a foolish,
inferior human being!

170
00:10:05,625 --> 00:10:08,791
Call me crazy, but I sense bias.

171
00:10:08,875 --> 00:10:11,750
Tohru, there is another
reason I'd rather not

172
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:13,250
let you fly me to work.

173
00:10:13,333 --> 00:10:14,458
[TOHRU]
Your back?

174
00:10:14,541 --> 00:10:17,833
Well, that's half of it.
The other half is--

175
00:10:19,416 --> 00:10:21,333
[KOBAYASHI]
You're too loud and too fast!

176
00:10:21,416 --> 00:10:24,291
I think a dragon's place is in
the home holding down the fort!

177
00:10:24,375 --> 00:10:25,833
Fort? What?

178
00:10:25,916 --> 00:10:28,333
You're one of the
stronger dragons, aren't you?

179
00:10:28,416 --> 00:10:30,458
If you consider
"starting Armageddon" strong.

180
00:10:30,541 --> 00:10:32,208
I do, and please don't.

181
00:10:32,291 --> 00:10:34,958
The world's dangerous enough
without your help.

182
00:10:35,041 --> 00:10:36,583
I'm just saying it would
be a relief to know

183
00:10:36,666 --> 00:10:38,583
you're here keeping
the house safe for me.

184
00:10:38,666 --> 00:10:41,125
[gasps]
Yes, I understand!

185
00:10:41,208 --> 00:10:42,958
So consider it done!

186
00:10:43,041 --> 00:10:44,500
So pretty.

187
00:10:44,583 --> 00:10:46,583
Well, I'm off to the office.

188
00:10:46,666 --> 00:10:47,916
If anybody calls,
you can answer

189
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,708
and take a message, yeah?

190
00:10:49,791 --> 00:10:50,708
[TOHRU]
What's a "calls"?

191
00:10:50,791 --> 00:10:52,208
Right, you're a dragon.

192
00:10:52,291 --> 00:10:53,833
This is a phone.

193
00:10:53,916 --> 00:10:56,000
When it goes "ring-ring,"
you pick it up like so.

194
00:10:56,083 --> 00:10:56,833
[TOHRU]
Okay, got it.

195
00:10:56,916 --> 00:10:58,291
They talk, then you talk.

196
00:10:58,375 --> 00:10:59,708
[TOHRU]
They talk, then I talk!

197
00:10:59,791 --> 00:11:02,250
--[KOBAYASHI] Okay, take care.
--[TOHRU] Save travels!

198
00:11:02,333 --> 00:11:03,958
[giggles]

199
00:11:04,041 --> 00:11:05,375
Hold the fort?

200
00:11:05,458 --> 00:11:08,500
[TOHRU snarls]

201
00:11:08,583 --> 00:11:11,291
Oh, is that what
those people were doing?

202
00:11:11,375 --> 00:11:13,208
I'll just ask Fafnir for help!

203
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:15,791
[FAFNIR]
Kill them.

204
00:11:15,875 --> 00:11:17,916
Kill all who try to
steal your treasure.

205
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,708
Kill all who are suspect.

206
00:11:19,791 --> 00:11:23,083
Curse them with death.
Curse their generations to come.

207
00:11:23,166 --> 00:11:25,791
He's always so helpful!
All right!

208
00:11:25,875 --> 00:11:29,250
Time to do my best to earn Miss
Kobayashi's love and praise!

209
00:11:29,333 --> 00:11:30,833
[lock rattling]

210
00:11:30,916 --> 00:11:32,458
[TOHRU]
Hmm?

211
00:11:32,541 --> 00:11:34,291
The lady who lives here
should be gone all day,

212
00:11:34,375 --> 00:11:35,625
but let's make this fast.

213
00:11:35,708 --> 00:11:39,541
We'll be in there
before you can say "open."

214
00:11:39,625 --> 00:11:41,083
[TOHRU growls]

215
00:11:41,166 --> 00:11:43,250
--[THIEF A] Uh.
--[TOHRU growls]

216
00:11:44,791 --> 00:11:47,041
[BOTH whimper]

217
00:11:48,458 --> 00:11:49,583
[screaming]

218
00:11:49,666 --> 00:11:50,958
[DOG barking]

219
00:11:52,666 --> 00:11:53,916
[THIEF A]
Save us!

220
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,333
--[KOBAYASHI] Hmm?
--[THIEF A] There's a monster!

221
00:11:55,416 --> 00:11:57,791
--[POLICE A] A monster?
--[THIEF B] We saw it, I swear!

222
00:11:57,875 --> 00:11:59,250
[KOBAYASHI]
I'm home.

223
00:11:59,333 --> 00:12:00,458
[TOHRU]
Welcome back!

224
00:12:00,541 --> 00:12:01,541
[KOBAYASHI]
Hold the fort down all right?

225
00:12:01,625 --> 00:12:03,375
[TOHRU]
I suppose, but it was lonely.

226
00:12:03,458 --> 00:12:04,500
--[KOBAYASHI] Ahh.
--[TOHRU] And I didn't even

227
00:12:04,583 --> 00:12:06,041
--get to kill them.
--[KOBAYASHI] Ahh.

228
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:07,166
Wait, what?

229
00:12:17,916 --> 00:12:20,166
[KOBAYASHI groans]

230
00:12:20,250 --> 00:12:21,916
[TAKIYA]
Hey, Kobayashi.

231
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,500
[KOBAYASHI]
What is it, Takiya?

232
00:12:23,583 --> 00:12:25,375
Want to grab some
drinks tonight?

233
00:12:25,458 --> 00:12:27,666
Sure, but, like, only one round.

234
00:12:29,833 --> 00:12:31,041
[KOBAYASHI]
So why me?

235
00:12:31,125 --> 00:12:32,375
There are plenty of
other girls you could ask.

236
00:12:32,458 --> 00:12:33,791
I don't want to go on a date.

237
00:12:33,875 --> 00:12:35,625
I asked you 'cause
you're like one of the guys.

238
00:12:35,708 --> 00:12:36,958
Wow, how sweet.

239
00:12:37,666 --> 00:12:38,875
[TOHRU growls]

240
00:12:38,958 --> 00:12:41,208
[TAKIYA] What's with
that girl staring us down?

241
00:12:41,291 --> 00:12:44,333
--Do you know her?
--Uh...

242
00:12:44,416 --> 00:12:47,875
Greetings, I'm Tohru Kobayashi.
Miss Kobayashi's new maid.

243
00:12:47,958 --> 00:12:51,708
Her new <i>live-in</i> maid.
New <i>violent</i> live-in maid.

244
00:12:51,791 --> 00:12:53,500
--[TAKIYA] Hmm.
--Yeah, it's my turn to

245
00:12:53,583 --> 00:12:55,208
take care of the
"special" cousin.

246
00:12:55,291 --> 00:12:56,916
I'm Makoto Takiya.

247
00:12:57,000 --> 00:13:00,375
Kobayashi and I work together.
